				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: nearing 39<a name="11303"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 8 03 11:12 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I would recomment Twilight desert, reasons being that
<br />
a) nothing there roots and casts (well nothing that wanders around)
<br />
b) the xp is nuts did 42 and 43 in 2 hours each, you will be able to do up to 47-48 there
<br />

<br />
What you do is head to the desert, then head up to the left. this is where you will be kiting. Now never ever attack the red and the blue alien dudes. They are on opposin factions but as long as you never attack a single one you will never have any problems.
<br />
Now the kiting part, Just do a quick run out into the desert, grab the flowers the lightcrawlers and the tigers all of these are fair game. The only guys to watch out for are the sunreavers (i think they are called that) they cast, you should be able to kill one on one unless he roots but as i said they dont wander, they have a small camp to the right of the zone in but its easily avoidable. 
<br />
Then once you grab up im guessing 10+ mobs head back and start running circles. At the time i didnt know how to swarm kite but this would be a great place to learn how as well if you want to try it.
<br />
Also keep your eyes out for the named mobs especially the &quot;glorious sunflower&quot; this thing drops a piece that will bag you the bravado breastplate (never ended up getting the d*mn thing)
<br />
And dont be scared, this site is a bards play ground.
<br />
PS no one is ever there so you wont have to deal with any mob stealing threats and what not</span></td>
